    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Collective term for large scale Japanese paintings pasted to wall surfaces of one sort or another, such as fusuma (sliding door panels); typically treating landscape, figural or bird-and-flower themes. It is often translated as "screen and wall paintings."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
